  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: \r\nafter sending messages from offline mode they are not shown in receiver chat even when 2 users are online.\r\nLog off\\log in process doesn't help.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nreceiver (user B) can see message (in my case \"Offline 2\") when sender goes online \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\noffline messages are lost\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status (user A)\r\n- Go to 1-1 Chat with another user (user B)\r\n- Switch on Airplane mode (user A)\r\n- Send message from offline mode (user A, with text i.e. \"Offline 2\")\r\nStatus should be \"Delivered\"\r\n- Switch off  Airplane mode(user A)\r\n- Open \"Chat\" screen (user B)\r\n- Wait until messages are getting synchronized (I waited for 5 min just in case).\r\nIn account of User B should appear  +1 message in 1-1 Chat with user A\r\n- Open chat with user A (user B). \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.12\r\n* Operating System: iOS 10.3.2\r\n\r\n#### Logs\r\n\r\n* Video: https://drive.google.com/open?id=1cIU4297suA1_0kONF09XVt0gxZkjB6RN",
